# Project Workflow

1. User uploads a skin image.
2. Flask backend receives the image.
3. Image preprocessing is performed.
4. MobileNetV2 model analyzes the image.
5. Disease prediction is generated.
6. Confidence score is calculated.
7. Disease details are displayed.
8. User location is collected.
9. Nearby hospitals are fetched using OpenStreetMap.
10. User can view nearby hospitals.
11. User can get navigation directions.
12. User can book appointments.
13. User can interact with the AI medical chatbot.
14. User can download or share reports.

---

# Model Details

## Model Used

1. MobileNetV2 with Transfer Learning.

## Why MobileNetV2?

1. Lightweight architecture.
2. Faster prediction speed.
3. Suitable for web deployment.
4. Good performance on limited datasets.

## Training Techniques

1. Data Augmentation.
2. Class Weighting.
3. Image Normalization.
4. Validation-Based Evaluation.

## Performance

1. Validation Accuracy: Approximately 70%.
2. Supports multi-class skin disease classification.

